<Review>Dirty environment. Last time I visited I couldn't help but be put off by the collection of filth under the equipment behind the register. While I witnessed employees doing there best to clean up spills they neglected to clean under the large metal equipment. I doubt their efforts could remove what looks like years of neglect. They'd probably have to replace the flooring to even remotely clean this area. Additionally the equipment the employees used looked filthy itself, concerning me over the true quality of cleanliness that their efforts could achieve in the areas they can reach to clean.

The place is always packed which surprises me as the quality of milk tea is lacking. I hear the chicken is good, but from what I've seen the product is nothing like what is advertised on the menu.

The boba itself is hit or miss, somedays it's perfect and others it's burnt. I'm not sure what they use in brewing the tea but I've become ill multiple times after consuming the product, once throwing up before I was able to leave the store having to run outside quickly to avoid causing another mess for the staff to clean.

My experience with the staff has been alright. They're often friendly. My order is usually what I place, except for one time in which a male staff member incorrectly prepared my order which I didn't notice till after I had already left.

With plenty of places in IV that have Boba I would absolutely recommend going elsewhere. The service is the only quality component at Wake Cup. Cleanliness and product are low quality, and advertisement on the menu is completely inaccurate.</Review>< pics>

<Name>Njushena< /Name><rating>1<//rating><review>We are very disappointed with our experience with the school.

My son's advanced belt (red with a black stripe) was taken away without any clear explanation. Instead he was given a white belt. A white belt after 4 years in Taekwondo! I emailed to the school asking to meet with Master Kim to discuss the issue. The request was declined with the words that Master Kim was not available for discussions.
In her email Mrs. Shannon stated that "Master Kim explained to all of the students at the beginning of class today, that if they are unable to perform at their belt level they will lose their belt.  If your son is confused he can check the Belt curriculum for what are the requirements for Red Advanced Belt.". That did not make sense neither to me nor to my son. He had always performed at maximum at Master Kim's classes. He had not had any discipline problems.

My son received the Red Advanced belt at Master Kim‚Äôs back in January 2017. Since then he's got about 15 black and red rewarding tapes on his belt, - that proves his diligence, not the opposite.
After the issue with the belt we made a decision to cancel our membership with MKTA. At the end of the last class I asked Shannon to return my son's belt. She refused to give it back saying that he had to regain the belt, despite she knew that was our last class with the school.

Not just for years of tuition, we have also paid fees for all the belt tests... only to end up with the white belt again. And no, we haven't gotten any money back.

After years at MKTA what value have we got for our money? Looks like NONE!
And if Master Kim is saying my son deserves only the white belt after 4 years at his school, isn't that Master Kim's failure?

You might ask, where are all these kids from the video that plays on the screen in the school‚Äôs window? - They all left and went to other schools! < review>
I go to Master Kim's Taekwondo Academy and love going there. Master Kim is so patient and encouraging. He makes sure to spend time with each student to help them use their bast potential. In class we do many activities. Some of them are Poomsaes (which are the forms taught in Taekwondo),  Board Breaking (when we break a board), Games, and Warm ups (like Push ups, Burpees, etc.). I have seen a big improvement in my discipline, focus and power. I would highly recommend people of all ages to go to this Taekwondo Academy to learn to fight and defend themselves.<//review>

< review>
I came to the office today for a TB skin test.  Full disclosure: English is not my first language (and my husband is helping me write this review).

Short version:  I wish I could give 0 stars for Dr. Masoud Mehraban.  He was the most arrogant and rude person I have ever interacted with.

Long version:  After being called back, a nurse (I think named Marge) was very patient with me and explained several times why I needed a chest x-ray instead of just a TB skin test like I thought.  Then when Dr. Mehraban came in, he asked perhaps the same questions but in a different way.  When I did not understand right away, he became irate and and started yelling at me.  "DO. YOU. UNDERSTAND. WHAT. I'M. SAYING?"  His voice was loud enough to carry through the whole office and the door to the examination room was open.  I was totally shocked by his lack of professionalism.  I didn't know what to say.  Since he has a slight accent, I can only assume that he is also an immigrant to this country, but his arrogance and rudeness were unforgivable.  Please avoid Dr. Mehraban at all costs.

Some free advice for Dr. Mehraban:  If you say the same thing three times progressively louder and a patient still does not understand, try saying it a different way.  Think about how you would feel if you went to a country where you did not speak the language fluently.</review>

< text>
Good place for a group. This time we had two long tables next to each other,  I'd say it's better than one LONG table that way. It made conversation much easier.

I was hungry, so this time I opted for the  Super Cinco, a combo of five  different meals in one: beef enchilada, chicken enchilada, beef taco, pork tamale, and chile relleno with a side of beans and rice. It took three plates to hold it all! I started with the tamale, and the corn meal crust was thick and juicy, just the way it should be. The rest of it was good, too. It took a while, but I managed to finish it all. :-)<//text>

< Review>
Update...its been 2 years...

I broght my niece here for her birthday...we made a reservation through yelp.  When we arrived we were seated right away.

It took a while for someone to come to our table to take the drink order. We were ready to put in our order instead of waiting.

While we were sitting there...we heard two of the staff openly say how much they hate there job...clearly...the service paired with the GROSS DIRTY DISHES prove there is no pride AT THIS PLACE...HORRIBLE...HORRIBLE.

I have been several times before...but it has been at least 2 years. I would not have come if she did not choose this place.

We ordered the mixed grilled fajitas to share...for the outrageous price of almost 27.00. Boy have the prices sky rocketed.

1. The chicken was so dry...neither of us wanted to eat it.
2. The steak was not good at all.
3. The shrimp and carnitas was very good.
4. It used to come with guacamole...they charge more and eliminated that.
5. It used to come with butter sauce for shrimp...did not get that...had to ask for it.

When we needed more tortillas...we saw our waitress for her to come...and she literally walked the other way.

This place has gone down hill...

No wonder their rating is only 3 star.

See my photos of dirty plate...no guac...no butter sauce for shrimp.

Never again.

I came here with my mom. The prices certainly have changed. We usually get the fajitas with all 4 meats to share. It came with beans... rice...meat...sour cream...guacamole...onions and peppers.

The price a couple months ago was 18.99. Now they are 24.99...same portion..but no more guacamole.

The menu advertises they are served flame ignited at the table...ours wasn't.

The flavor was good...but very disappointed at price increase...minus guacamole..not flame ignited as advertised. I like their food...but if I did not have a birthday coupon..I would not spend 25.00 for this. I just font think it is worth it. 18.00...I got that several times...but 25.00...I would spend that same money elsewhere.  It's a shame there was such a huge price increase for less food...üò≠üò≠üò≠</Review>

<review>Update! 1/14/20

Was served in the bar during Happy Hour by Casey G. As in Greeted immediately, as in Great service, as in Gonna come back next week and ask for him.

In a very very busy bar with what we confirmed had only one server, and at least 14 tables, we were well taken care of. As if there were three servers on duty. Very attentive, stopping to answer any question or concern that we have. Double checking on the quality of food not only for us for tables around us. As a very heavy contrast we had recent experiences that were less than pleasant. One was so difficult that we weren‚Äôt even seated, and had our party leaving frustrated. His bar knowledge only improved his serving skills further and the quality of the food matched the skill of Casey. We will come back sooner than normal.

The food. The drinks. The Service!
.

.

<user>101984509891157809742<//user>< Text>
I have gone to Chevy's a few times and the service was standard, but I had to leave a review for my experience this time around because of our amazing server, Samantha, or Sam, I think, is what she went by. Me and my friends walked in and got seated right away. A bubbly, red headed server, Sam, walked over to our table and greeted us with a huge genuine smile. She took our drink orders, and came back pretty quickly, along with chips and salsa. She was always very perceptive to our table (even though she had a few others as well), and was great at multi tasking. She gave us enough time to look over the menu and took our orders with an enthusiastic demeanor (very genuine). I threw a curve ball at her and was torn between a few menu items. I asked her what she liked/preferred, and without hesitation, gave her recommendations (based off a few opened ended questions from her-to make it easier on the both of us). She recommended the chicken fajita plate, and it was delish! Thank you Sam and Chevys for the amazing customer service. I recommend this place and especially Sam.</Text>

Update! 1/14/20

Was served in the bar during Happy Hour by Casey G. As in Greeted immediately, as in Great service, as in Gonna come back next week and ask for him.

In a very very busy bar with what we confirmed had only one server, and at least 14 tables, we were well taken care of. As if there were three servers on duty. Very attentive, stopping to answer any question or concern that we have. Double checking on the quality of food not only for us for tables around us. As a very heavy contrast we had recent experiences that were less than pleasant. One was so difficult that we weren‚Äôt even seated, and had our party leaving frustrated. His bar knowledge only improved his serving skills further and the quality of the food matched the skill of Casey. We will come back sooner than normal.

The food. The drinks. The Service!
.
Everything was amazing start to finish, our server Frederic made the experience what it was. The food is always great quality, but the pacing and drinks and attentiveness is something that differs server to server, needless to say we will always be asking if Frederic‚Äôs section is an option.
.
Happy hour had a great variety of food and drinks, and I was thrilled to find I could order a single enchilada when I wanted to try something new. Thanks Chevys!<//text>

< Review>
I've always been big fan of Chevy's for over 20 years and this location is no exception. The food is always good and the portions are pretty big. I tend to eat a lot and I almost always have something left over to bring home. In our most recent visit, it was a fairly busy weekend in the holiday season and it the latter part of the dinner hour, but we were not down immediately at a booth. They provided a kid's menu with crayons for our two-year-old. And the food was ready very quickly. I think our server was a little new, but I would still recommend Chevy's every time.<//Review>

< text>
I have been a Chevy's patron for many many years. I don't know if this location is under new management, has a new chef, or habe just changed their standards again, but I was very disappointed in my Nacho Grande. I asked for extra of the red sauce and wound up with a totally different red/orange sauce that did not complement the dish at all. The cheese and meat were basically one thin layer and left me with a plate full of untouched chips.
Normally I would rate Chevy's with at least 4 stars, but this time they barely hit the 3 star mark.
I hope this was just a fluke, otherwise my long lived loyalty will be gone.<//text>
